fillFunctions() - Static method in class sudokuGame.Individual
Load all the functions names in functions ArrayList, these all the functions that we support in the Terminals, the Terminals exist only and only in the leaves of the Tree-Based Genetic Programing.

If you decide to support other functions or to choose specific functions, you can use this method.
fillOperators() - Static method in class sudokuGame.Individual
Load all the operators names in operators ArrayList, these all the functions that we support in the Primitive, the Primitive can exist almost in any Node in the Tree-Based Genetic Programing.
fillOperators(ArrayList<String>) - Static method in class sudokuGame.Individual
If you decide to support other operators or to choose specific operators, you can use this method.
findHeight() - Method in class sudokuGame.Individual
Be careful before using this method , this method is calculate the tree height in recourse way, we use it only and only when we do crossover between two trees, so we can calculate in runtime the height of the new tree to update height field.
findHeight() - Method in class sudokuGame.Node
Finds the height of the tree (longest path from the root to any leaf).
findLeftHeight() - Method in class sudokuGame.Node
Finds the height of the left child tree, use findTreeHeight recursive function.
findRightHeight() - Method in class sudokuGame.Node

findTreeHeight(Node<T>) - Method in class sudokuGame.Node
